I know `IsTraitEnabled` should be moved, but should `IDisabledTrait` be removed and/or use overriding `IsTraitEnabled` instead of `IsTraitDisabled` with `IsTraitEnabled` returning true by default from `Trait` abstract base class.

``` c#
public abstract class Trait<TTraitInfo>
{
    public readonly TTraitInfo Info;
    public virtual bool IsTraitEnabled() { return true; }

    /// <summary>Use for filtering; ex: .Where(Trait.IsEnabled)</summary>
    public static bool IsEnabled(Trait t) { return t.IsTraitEnabled(); }

    public Trait(TTraitInfo info) { Info = info; }
}
```

One reason to keep `IDisabledTrait.IsTraitDisabled` as `DisableableTrait.IsTraitDisabled`. is:

``` c#
public abstract class DisableableTrait : Trait
{
    public override bool IsTraitEnabled() { return !IsTraitDisabled; }
    public abstract bool IsTraitDisabled { get; }
    // -OR-
    public override bool IsTraitEnabled() { return !IsTraitDisabled(); }
    public abstract bool IsTraitDisabled();
}
```

which requires `IsTraitDisabled` to be overridden.
